The paper deals with the evaluation of regular path queries (RPQs) in graph databases, which is a central problem in the field of database management systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the enumeration of paths in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science, and hence, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the parameterized complexity of the problem, which could be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
